**Abstract:**
Essay dated September 3, 1996 titled "On Truth and Statements." Opens with Macbeth quotation on perception and Kerferd on Socratic knowledge. Argues that medieval theory of knowledge as judgments misinterprets how statements function. Distinguishes practical existential knowledge (self-referential, terminating in action) from scientific predicative knowledge (purely objective, terminating in assent).

**AI Recommendation:** Major epistemological essay; precedes 96-SEP-2 on epistemic subject.

